  "title": "Simple circuits - does S1 or S2 light the bulb",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a circuit diagram with a battery, a lightbulb, two switches, and a resistor. The battery B is on the top edge. Immediately to the right of the battery, the circuit splits into two vertical branches. The middle vertical branch has switch S sub 2. The right vertical branch has lightbulb L. Between the left and middle vertical branches, the bottom horizontal branch has resistor R. The left vertical branch has switch S sub 1.\" src=\"/images/dae963d5fdf8b1f4daeb64b08981b0db.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The circuit shown contains a battery <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, a lightbulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></math></span></span>, a resistor <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></math></span></span>, and two switches <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S sub 1\"><math alttext=\"S sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mtext>S</mtext><mtext>1</mtext></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S sub 2\"><math alttext=\"S sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mtext>S</mtext><mtext>2</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>. Both switches are initially open. Which switch must be closed in order for the lightbulb to light, and what evidence or reasoning supports the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> must be closed. The resistor is not part of a closed electrical loop if Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is open.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> must be closed. The battery is not part of a closed electrical loop if Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is open.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> must be closed. The bulb is not in a loop by itself if Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is open.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> must be closed. The bulb does not have two paths to the battery if Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is open.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
